data.title: How many lawyers were eligible to practice law in cities in Sangamon County in July?
data.meta_description: The number of lawyers with active licenses in cities in Sangamon County in July decreased in comparison to the previous month.
data.text:
Cities within Sangamon County had a decline in the number of lawyers with active licenses compared to the previous month, according to the ARDC of the Supreme Court of Illinois.

In total, there were 586 active legal licenses recorded in cities in Sangamon County in July, compared to 587 in the previous month.

The majority of these active licenses were granted in Springfield (575).

A 2023 study found Illinois had the fourth-highest number of lawyers per capita in the United States, with nearly five lawyers per 1,000 residents.

As of 2024, the average salary for a lawyer in Illinois averages around $104,889 annually, which is fairly close to the national average.

Data refers to all lawyers who were actively practicing during this period.
